<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="isreal">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>isreal</refname>
    <refpurpose>  check if a variable as real or complex entries</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>t=isreal(x)
t=isreal(x,eps)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>x</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>vector or matrix with floating point entries or coefficients</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>t</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a boolean</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para><literal>isreal(x)</literal> returns true if <literal>x</literal> is stored as a real variable and
    false if  <literal>x</literal> is stored with an (eventually zero) imaginary part.</para>
    <para><literal>isreal(x,eps)</literal> returns true if <literal>x</literal> is stored as a real variable or
    if maximum absolute value of imaginary floating points is less or equal
    than <literal>eps</literal>.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[

isreal([1 2])
isreal(1+0*%i)
isreal(1+0*%i,0)
isreal(1+%s)
isreal(sprand(3,3,0.1))
 
  ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
</refentry>
